These are the criteria that were mentioned in one of the previous questions https://t.co/gJ80wvfXJa
Draghi: The programme is running smoothly and it has enough flexibility
Draghi: Economic and Monetary Union is incomplete, new work on completing it is to be welcomed
Draghi: We need to be persistent, we need to accompany the recovery with our monetary policy
Draghi: We are confident inflation will converge to our objective in a durable way
Draghi: We need to be patient and we need to be confident
Draghi: Other policy areas must contribute much more decisively to strengthening economic growth
Draghi: Measures since June 2014 continue to significantly support borrowing conditions for firms, including SMEs, and households
Draghi: HICP projections: 1.5% in 2017 [1.7% in March], 1.3% in 2018 [1.6%] and 1.6% in 2019 [1.7%]
Draghi: GDP projections: 1.9% in 2017 [1.8% in March], 1.8% in 2018 [1.7%], 1.7% in 2019 [1.6%]
Draghi: Economic growth prospects continue to be dampened by a sluggish pace of implementation of structural reforms
Draghi: If needed, we stand ready to increase our asset purchase programme in terms of size and/or duration
Draghi: Very substantial degree of accommodation still needed for underlying inflation pressures to build up and support headline inflation
Draghi: Economic expansion has yet to translate into stronger inflation dynamics. Underlying inflation continues to remain subdued.
Draghi: We consider that the risks to the growth outlook are now broadly balanced
Draghi: Information since our last monetary policy meeting confirms a stronger momentum in the euro area economy
Draghi: Net asset purchases to run until end of Dec 2017, or beyond, if needed, until we see a sustained adjustment in inflation
Draghi: We expect rates to remain at their present levels for an extended period of time, and well past horizon of our net asset purchases
